+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:93:| CCH-013 | Implement R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH): parabolic tempo + loudness arch over each phrase, modulated by section envelope. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/phrase_arch.py` computes tempo_mult(x) = 1 + k·(-4·(x-peak)² + 1)·tempo_deviation_pct/100 and matching amp_mult for normalized phrase position x<br/>- defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, peak=0.6, k=1.0<br/>- arc_shape parameter supports parabolic, cosine, asymmetric-Bezier, flat, inverted variants<br/>- composes multiplicatively with SectionEnvelope.tempo_base at each event<br/>- tests verify arc shape, peak position, and multiplicative composition |
+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:105:| CCH-025 | Implement R11 Call-Response Gating: follower phrase intent complements leader's realized performance. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/call_response.py` reads leader voice's PerformedPart and transforms follower's PerformanceIntent before follower render<br/>- leader build → follower descends from apex; leader pause → follower fills<br/>- respects existing role metadata (leader/follower/solo/tacet) from production-course PRD<br/>- tests verify complementarity on 2-voice fixture |
+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:106:| CCH-026 | Compose SectionEnvelope with phrase arcs multiplicatively so section-level tempo elasticity modulates phrase-level shaping. | MUST | T1 | - at each event, final_tempo_mult = section_envelope.tempo_base(t) × phrase_arch.tempo_mult(x) × (1 + sensor_tempo_scale)<br/>- clamp composed result to ±15% bounds<br/>- tests verify multiplicative composition and clamp behavior |
+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:108:| CCH-028 | Add arc-shape variety so not every phrase uses a symmetric parabola: per-phrase random selection from parabolic/cosine/asymmetric-Bezier/flat/inverted with peak-position variance. | MUST | T1 | - arc_shape selected from PerformanceIntent or, if unspecified, sampled from authored distribution weighted by intent_tag<br/>- for intent_tag=withhold, occasional flat arc (tempo_deviation_pct=0) is expressive<br/>- tests verify shape distribution over many phrases and flat-arc presence for withhold intent |
+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:109:| CCH-029 | Implement restraint parameter enforced as global dampener across rules. | MUST | T1 | - PerformanceIntent.restraint ∈ [0, 1] scales: tempo_deviation_pct (× (1-restraint)), dynamic_range_db (× (1-restraint·0.7)), silence-budget thresholds (× (1 + restraint))<br/>- R2, R10 read restraint at runtime<br/>- tests verify restraint=0 is neutral and restraint=1 produces near-flat phrases with extended silence |
+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:112:| CCH-032 | Couple narrative engine to SectionEnvelope selection so dramatic arcs drive section choice. | SHOULD | T2 | - narrative beat → SectionEnvelope mapping exposed via existing narrative engine interface<br/>- section choice respects tension_trajectory + tone_vector from narrative tone controller<br/>- tests use fixture beats and verify expected section envelopes selected |
+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:119:| CCH-039 | Embed rule-stack provenance in exported audio metadata (e.g., WAV iXML chunk or sidecar JSON) for listener-review workflow. | MUST | T1 | - each rendered audio file gets a `.render.json` sidecar with Event list, rule_stack per event, PerformanceIntent per phrase, SectionEnvelope per section, seeds, delta_track path<br/>- format documented in `my-claw/docs/render-audio-sidecar.md`<br/>- tests verify sidecar presence, schema, and ability to replay from sidecar alone |
